# N8N Student Kit — Project Context

Self-hosted n8n automation stack wrapped in a Windows GUI. Live on GitHub:
https://github.com/Phill1983/N8N-Student-Kit (branch `main`).

## Repo layout

```
N8N-Workstation/
├── .cursor/rules/             # these context rules
├── .gitignore
├── README.md                  # English README (primary)
├── README.uk.md               # Ukrainian README
│
├── n8n-student-kit/           # backend + legacy WinForms GUI
│   ├── install.bat            # admin-level installer w/ auto-download of tools
│   ├── start.bat / stop.bat
│   ├── gui-run.cmd            # headless wrapper the GUIs call
│   ├── N8N-Student-Kit-GUI.ps1  # WinForms GUI (classic alternative, KEEP)
│   ├── start-gui.bat / .vbs   # launchers for WinForms GUI
│   ├── compose/docker-compose.yml
│   ├── templates/             # env + ngrok templates
│   ├── tools/                 # GITIGNORED: Docker installer, ngrok.exe, images/*.tar
│   └── state/                 # GITIGNORED: .env, install.cfg, *.log
│
└── n8n-student-kit-preview/   # primary WPF GUI (Fluent dark theme)
    ├── MainWindow.xaml
    ├── N8N-Student-Kit-WPF.ps1
    ├── start-wpf.bat / .vbs
    └── README.md              # WPF-specific design notes
```

## Two GUIs, one backend

Both GUIs share `state/install.cfg`, `state/.env`, and call the same `.bat` files.
Users can switch between WinForms and WPF freely without losing config.

| GUI | Stack | Status |
|---|---|---|
| `N8N-Student-Kit-GUI.ps1` | WinForms + GDI+ | legacy, still works, kept as lightweight alternative |
| `N8N-Student-Kit-WPF.ps1` | WPF + XAML, PowerShell 5.1 | **primary**, dark Fluent theme |

## Key technical decisions

- **Windows-only** (PowerShell + WPF). macOS/Linux port = future (Avalonia UI candidate).
- **PowerShell 5.1** baseline (built-in on Win 10/11). Don't use PS 7-only features.
- **XAML loaded via `XamlReader.Load`** from a string read with UTF-8 (never `Get-Content -Raw` without `-Encoding UTF8` — it breaks unicode on 5.1).
- **Icon, logo, progress bar, scrollbar, lightning bolt** — all drawn programmatically via `DrawingVisual` / XAML geometry. NO external image assets.
- **AppUserModelID** set via P/Invoke `shell32!SetCurrentProcessExplicitAppUserModelID` to prevent taskbar grouping with other `powershell.exe` windows.
- **DPI awareness** via P/Invoke `shcore!SetProcessDpiAwareness(2)` with `user32!SetProcessDPIAware` fallback.
- **`install.bat` auto-downloads** Docker Desktop Installer and ngrok from official sources if missing in `tools/`. Offline install: drop files manually, auto-detected. curl first, PowerShell `Invoke-WebRequest` fallback.
- **Silent launch** via `.vbs` files (hides PS console window entirely).
- **AUTO_REUSE flag** in `install.bat` suppresses interactive prompts when invoked from the GUI.

## Guardrails

- **NEVER commit** `state/*.env`, `state/install.cfg`, or `tools/*.exe`/`*.tar` — they contain secrets or are giant binaries. `.gitignore` enforces this.
- **NEVER use `Get-Content -Raw`** on XAML without explicit UTF-8 encoding; use `[IO.File]::ReadAllText($path, [Text.Encoding]::UTF8)`.
- **Geometry from `Geometry.Parse(...)`** is frozen — apply transforms via `DrawingContext.PushTransform`, not `geom.Transform = ...`.
- **FormattedText constructors**: use the 7-arg version `(text, culture, flowDir, typeface, emSize, brush, pixelsPerDip=96)` for WPF 4.6+ safety.
- **Unicode glyphs in XAML**: digits work in `Segoe UI Variable`, but icons (`0xE700+`) need `FontFamily="Segoe MDL2 Assets"`. Don't mix; if unsure, use plain Unicode (`✓` U+2713) that any font renders.
- **In `Set-Step`** always reset `$icon.Text` explicitly — otherwise state transitions leave stale glyphs.

## Running the app locally

```cmd
n8n-student-kit-preview\start-wpf.vbs
```

Flow in GUI: Save → Install (Admin) (twice: Docker then rest) → Start.

## Git workflow

- Default branch: `main`. Remote: `origin` = `https://github.com/Phill1983/N8N-Student-Kit.git`.
- Conventional commits style: `feat(scope): ...`, `fix(scope): ...`, `docs: ...`.
- Credentials: Git Credential Manager (OAuth). Already authenticated locally.

